==English==
===Etymology===
From the [[exclamation]] ''oh my Goddess!'', originally an invocation for the help of a goddess.  Cf. the masculine variant [[oh my God]].

===Expression===
'''oh my Goddess!'''

# an interjection uttered when an event or statement is beyond belief.
#:''Oh my Goddess, I cannot believe that just crawled out of the sink!''

===Usage notes===
Frequently used by Wiccans.

